{{Infobox figure skater |name= Judianne Fotheringill |image= |caption= |fullname= Judianne Fotheringill |altname= |country= [[United States]] |formercountry= |birth_date= {{birth date and age|1944|7|21}} |birth_place= [[Chehalis, Washington]] |hometown= |residence= |death_date= |death_place= |height= {{convert|170|cm|ft|abbr=on}} |partner= [[Jerry Fotheringill]] |formerpartner= |coach= |formercoach= |choreographer= |formerchoreographer= |skating club= [[Broadmoor SC]] |retired= }} '''Judianne "Judi" Fotheringill''' (born July 21, 1944 in [[Chehalis, Washington]]) is an [[United States|American]] [[pair skater]]. With brother [[Jerry Fotheringill]], she is the 1963 and 1964 [[United States Figure Skating Championships|U.S. national champion]]. They represented the [[United States at the 1964 Winter Olympics]] where [[figure skating at the 1964 Winter Olympics|they placed 7th]].
The Fotheringills were originally from [[Tacoma, Washington]] but later relocated to train in [[Colorado Springs, Colorado]], where they represented the [[Broadmoor Skating Club]]. Judi attended [[Colorado College]] during the time she was competing. She was tall for a pair skater at 5'7"; her brother, three years her senior, was 5'11".<ref>"1963 North American, U.S., & Canadian Champions", ''Skating'' magazine, May 1963</ref>
